# Keep the Docker build context small and free of secrets/cruft. The build does
# `COPY . .`, so anything not excluded here is shipped to the daemon (and into the
# build stage). The final image only carries the binary + LICENSE/NOTICE, but a
# tight context is faster and avoids leaking local state into intermediate layers.

# Version control + CI metadata (the binary is stamped via build-args, not VCS).
.git
.github
.gitignore

# Build artifacts / release output.
build/
dist/
coverage.out
cadish

# Editor / OS / tooling junk and anything that could carry local secrets.
.idea
.vscode
*.log
*.pem
*.key
.env
.env.*
node_modules
